      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIVA'S ROSE (3) shapes well after a swift run last time, finishing second in a Grade 5 at Ballarat in 22.23. Has the ability and looks a key chance again. LEKTRA HOPPER (7) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.13) at Mt Gambier behind Compton Chinook in a TG1-4W. Has the pace to be prominent. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Hard to beat again. NAPIER BALE (1) drew a squeeze box and was game in defeat when a close second, a neck from the winner Dimora Blitz (23.58) at Horsham. Expected to be in this for a long way. XISAN BALE (2) was in the money last start at big odds - poses a threat again.",
